Calculate beta diversity and PCos. I am using log transformed relative abundances because I couldnt use DESeq2 to normalize the whole dataset. This was because there is no single OTU with at least one count in all the samples, a requirement to run the default pipeline.

dist <- beta_div_dist(otu.ra %>% log_norm)

Plot the dendogram and taxonomic profiles

dd.row <- as.dendrogram(hclust(as.dist(dist), method = "average"))
ddata_x <- dendro_data(dd.row)
dendro.p <- ggplot(segment(ddata_x)) +
  geom_segment(aes(x=x, y=-y, xend=xend, yend=-yend))
labs <- label(ddata_x) %>% 
  inner_join(map, by = c("label" = "SampleID"))
Column `label`/`SampleID` joining factor and character vector, coercing into character vector
phy.ra <- otu.ra.tidy %>% 
  inner_join(tax) %>% 
  group_by(SampleID, PhyClass2) %>%
  summarise(Total = sum(Count)) %>% 
  group_by(SampleID) %>% 
  mutate(RelAb = (Total/sum(Total))) %>% 
  inner_join(map, by = "SampleID") %>% 
  select(SampleID, PhyClass2, RelAb)
Joining, by = "OTU_ID"
phy.ra <- inner_join(labs, phy.ra,  by = c("label" = "SampleID"))

Visaulize them separately. In these analyses I used variance stabilizing transformed counts as the clustering with this approach was neater First experiment

map1 <- filter(map, Study == "Expt1")
otu1 <- otu[,colnames(otu) %in% map1$SampleID]
dds1 <- DESeqDataSetFromMatrix(otu1,
                                colData = map1,
                                design = ~ Soil + Inoculum)
converting counts to integer mode
some variables in design formula are characters, converting to factorsfactor levels were dropped which had no samples
vsd1 <- varianceStabilizingTransformation(dds1, blind = FALSE) %>% assay
vsd1[vsd1 < 0.0] <- 0.0
dist1 <- beta_div_dist(vsd1)
pcoa.axes1 <- pcoa_axes(dist1, map1)
pcoa.eigval1 <- pcoa_eigval(dist1, map1)
